<h2>Some of the Cons are</h2>

<ul>
  <li><h3>Risk of disease!</h3>The swarm left its old home because it was over crowded. If the hive came from a beekeeper it was because they were not managed properly. They were not provided with space soon enough. When things are really happening this can be hard to do. Especially when numbers go up. The risk comes from the hive it came from not being monitored properly. This appiles to 'feral' hives. There are no truly wild hives in North America.</li>
  <li><h3>Poor genetics</h3>The process of swarming is the honey bees means of reproduction. Can work good for the bees. Certainly dose not work for beekeepers. Bees prone to swarming are a problem to beekeepers.<a href="http://beemaster.ca/cgi-bin/index.cgi?site=BMaster&page=SwarmControl" target="_blank" name="SwarmControl"></a></li>
</ul>

